    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "At first glance, Tic Tac Toe may seem like a simple game of chance, but it's far from it. A skilled player can always force a draw or even win if their opponent makes a mistake. The key to winning lies in understanding the game's strategy:"
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "ul",
      "property": null,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "li",
          "property": null,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "property": null,
              "children": "The Center Square: "
            },
            {
              "type": "span",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Occupying the center square gives you the most strategic advantage, as it allows you to control more potential winning combinations."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "li",
          "property": null,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Corner Moves: "
            },
            {
              "type": "span",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Taking a corner square is also a strong move, as it provides multiple paths to victory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "li",
          "property": null,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Blocking Moves: "
            },
            {
              "type": "span",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Pay attention to your opponent's moves and be ready to block their potential wins."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "li",
          "property": null,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "property": null,
              "children": "Forking Moves: "
            },
            {
              "type": "span",
              "property": null,
              "children": "If you're playing as 'X', creating a situation where you have two potential winning moves on your next turn (a fork) forces your opponent into a defensive position."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
